    "138242753": {
      "title": "Aggregate stability and size distribution",
      "abstract": "An aggregate is a group of primary particles that cohere to each other ::: more strongly than to other surrounding soil particles. Most adjacent ::: particles adhere to some degree. Therefore, disintegration of the soil mass ::: into aggregates requires imposition of a disrupting force. Stability of aggregates ::: is a function of whether the cohesive forces between particles ::: withstand the applied disruptive force."
